Prerequisites
Ensure that you have the following installed on your machine:

Git
Docker
Docker Compose

Cloning the Repository
To clone the repository, open your terminal and run the following command:

Copy code
git clone https://github.com/mestrada2023/CPPlaywrightTest.git


Setting Up Docker
The project is containerized and can be run using Docker Compose. The docker-compose.yml file in the root of the repository defines the services for both the frontend and backend.

1. Build and Run
Commands below - 
(a) docker-compose up --build -d
This is to run web, api and playwright tests
(b) npx playwright test
This is to run the automation test
2. npx playwright show-report --port=9324
This is to show the report


Stopping the Containers
To stop the containers, press CTRL+C in the terminal where docker-compose up is running. Alternatively, you can stop them by running:
docker-compose down
